definition.val: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.
Temporal interval that defines gorilla life from the prenatal stage until late adult stage.
Gorilla life cycle that starts with fertilization and ends at birth.
Gorilla developmental stage that covers the period from birth until about 8 years old, when individuals reach sexual maturity.

comments: Gorilla reach sexual maturity by 4015 days of age for male, 2829 days for female (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Gorilla_gorilla).

definition.val: Gorilla developmental stage that covers the period from birth until about 2 years old, at which point individuals usually wean.
Gorilla developmental stage that covers the period from about 2 years old, when individuals wean, until about 8 years old, when individuals reach sexual maturity.

comments: Gorilla reach sexual maturity by 4015 days of age for male, 2829 days for female (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Gorilla_gorilla).

definition.val: Gorilla developmental stage that refers to a sexually mature adult gorilla, which is usually over about 8 years old.
Mature stage that refers to a gorilla who is over about 8 and under 30 years old.

comments: Geriatric gorillas are defined as animals with 30 years of age and older (see http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs10764-006-9097-1).

definition.val: Mature stage that refers to a gorilla who is over 30 years old.

comments: Geriatric gorillas are defined as animals with 30 years of age and older (see http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs10764-006-9097-1). Maximum longevity is officially 55.4 years (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Gorilla_gorilla).

Count of number of days intervening between the end of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first day of development has the value of 1 for this property.

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.

definition.val: Count of number of months intervening between the end of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first month of development has the value of 1 for this property, and the period during which the organism is one month old has the value 2

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.

definition.val: Count of number of years intervening between the end of the stage and the time of birth according to a reference model. Note that the first year of post-birth development has the value of 1 for this property, and the period during which the child is one year old has the value 2

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.

Subset consisting of classes describing highly granular developmental stages (for instance, '23-year-old'). Such stages might be useful for annotation purpose, but might be folded into less granular parents for display purpose.
Used to associate a measurement property (e.g. days post fertilization) with a unit (e.g. days)

definition.val: Count of number of days intervening between the start of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first day of development has the value of 0 for this property.

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.

definition.val: Count of number of months intervening between the start of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first month of development has the value of 1 for this property, and the period during which the organism is one month old has the value 1.

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.

definition.val: Count of number of years intervening between the start of the stage and the time of birth according to a reference model. Note that the first year of post-birth development has the value of 0 for this property, and the period during which the child is one year old has the value 1.

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.
